The determination of the elemental composition of lignite fines and P-HAS and M-HAS was done by CHNS Unicube model analyser (Elementar Analysen systeme GmbH, Germany). The carbon (C), hydrogen (H), nitrogen (N) and sulphur (S) were directly taken from the analysis and the determination of the amount of oxygen (O) was calculated by formula i.e. % O = 100% − (%C + %H + %N + %S) after taking into account the ash yield of lignite and derived materials. The elemental analysis of all the samples was summarized in Table 2. On the basis of elemental value, the atomic ratio H/C, O/C and C/N were calculated. Mineral matter (MM) content was calculated using the Parr formula:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
